{"lemma":"عَمِّ","slug":"عَمِّ","root":"ع.م.م","root_slug":"ع-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَمّ","root":"عمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","particle","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30444","n30454","n30451","n30453","n30455","n30619"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"particle","gloss":"from what?"},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"about what?","examples":[{"text":"عَمَّ يَتَسَاءَلُونَ","english":"About what are they asking one another?"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become general"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spread, to prevail","examples":[{"text":"هُنَالِكَ عَمَّ ٱلْخَيْرُ","english":"The good spread there."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to comprise, to include, to encompass, to pervade","examples":[{"text":"عَمَّ ٱلْمَطَرُ ٱلْأَرْضَ","english":"The rain encompassed the whole land."},{"text":"عَمَّهُمُ ٱلْمَرَضُ","english":"The disease spread among them."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to extend, to stretch, to be diffused, to be prevailing"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paternal blood uncle (one's father's brother)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"term of address to an older person","tags":["informal"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blind","examples":[{"text":"بَلِ ٱدَّارَكَ عِلْمُهُمْ فِي ٱلْآخِرَةِ ۚ بَلْ هُمْ فِي شَكٍّ مِنْهَا ۖ بَلْ هُم مِنْهَا عَمُونَ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From عَن (ʕan) + مَا (mā).\n\nCompare Hebrew עַם (am, “nation, people”)."},"ipa":["/ʕamm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30444","headword_ar":"عَمَّ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuwmN","text_ar":"عُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$amila AljamaAEapa","text_ar":"شَمِلَ الجَمَاعَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universally, comprehensive: it included the common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole, aggregate, assemblage, bulk, mass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extent, within its compass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within the compass of its relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations, its effect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effects, its operation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"operations, its influence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: said of a thing: (S, K:) of rain, &c.: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuwmN","text_ar":"عُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"including,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the generality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(PS:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occurring, to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the generality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~a","text_ar":"عَمَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuw^abaA='u Aln~aAEisi","text_ar":"ثُوَبَا=ءُ النَّاعِسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The yawning of the drowsy became common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov., applied to the case of an event that happens in a town, or country, and then extends from it to the other towns, or countries. (TA.) ―         -b2-  It is also trans. [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, included, comprehended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embraced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"persons, or things,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in common, in general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universally, within the compass of his action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"influence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within the compass of its relation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations, its effect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effects, its operation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"operations, its influence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and when trans., its inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~N","text_ar":"عَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TK.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~a AlmaTaru AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"عَمَّ المَطَرُ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rain included the general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the whole, extent of the land within the compass of its fall"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (The Lexicons passim.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~ahumo biAlEaTiy~api","text_ar":"عَمَّهُمْ بِالعَطِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He included them in common, in general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universally, within the compass of the gift;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave to them in common, in general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universally"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~a fiY","text_ar":"عَمَّ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duEaAy^ihi waxaS~a","text_ar":"دُعَايِهِ وَخَصَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He included,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"persons or things"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in general, in his prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplication"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and particularized,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"specified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"some person or thing, or some persons or things]. (S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xal~a","text_ar":"خَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~ahumu AlmaraDu","text_ar":"عَمَّهُمُ المَرَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The disease was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universal, among them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (The Lexicons passim.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~a","text_ar":"عَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, made long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)       -A3-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became a paternal uncle"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra Eam~FA","text_ar":"صَارَ عَمًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":").] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kunotu Eam~FA walaqado","text_ar":"مَا كُنْتُ عَمًّا وَلَقَدْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamimotu","text_ar":"عَمِمْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was not a paternal uncle, and now I have become a paternal uncle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (so in my copies of the S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kunota Eam~FA walaqado Eamimota","text_ar":"مَا كُنْتَ عَمًّا وَلَقَدْ عَمِمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamamota","text_ar":"عَمَمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou wast not"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (so accord. to different copies of the K: the former accord. to the TK [agreeably with my copies of the S; and this I believe to be the right reading, or at least preferable; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amimotu","text_ar":"اَمِمْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuwmapN","text_ar":"عُمُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuw^uwlapN","text_ar":"خُوُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umuwmapN","text_ar":"اُمُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubuw~apN","text_ar":"اُبُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoniY wabayona fulaAnK EumuwmapN","text_ar":"بَيْنِى وَبَيْنَ فُلَانٍ عُمُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between me and such a one is a relationship of paternal uncle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eum~a","text_ar":"عُمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","PS"]},{"entry_id":"n30454","headword_ar":"عَمَّ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~a yatasaA='aluwna","text_ar":"عَمَّ يَتَسَا=ءَلُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Respecting what do they ask one another?"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur lxxviii. 1] is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~aA","text_ar":"عَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano maA","text_ar":"عَنْ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being elided in the interrogation [after the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30451","headword_ar":"عَمَ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamaA","text_ar":"عَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA","text_ar":"اَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see this last, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AmA","text_ar":"اما"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30453","headword_ar":"عَمٌّ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a tribe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a numerous company;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEam~N","text_ar":"اَعَمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) this latter mentioned by AAF, on the authority of AZ, and said by him to be the only instance of a word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEal","text_ar":"اَفْعَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting a plurality, unless it be a [coll.] gen. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruwaY","text_ar":"اَرُوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he cites as an ex. the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona","text_ar":"بَيْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEam~","text_ar":"الاَعَمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a verse; but Fr is related to have read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byn AlA^aEum~i","text_ar":"بين الاَعُمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":", making it pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~N","text_ar":"عَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDob~N","text_ar":"اَضْبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~N","text_ar":"ضَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A paternal uncle; a father's brother:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomaAmN","text_ar":"اَعْمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuwmN","text_ar":"عُمُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumuwmapN","text_ar":"عُمُومَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEim~apN","text_ar":"اَعِمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEum~N","text_ar":"اَعُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) a pl. of pauc., mentioned by Fr and IAar, (TA,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomumuwna","text_ar":"اَعْمُمُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) without idghám, by rule"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEum~uwna","text_ar":"اَعُمُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the female is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~apN","text_ar":"عَمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a paternal aunt; a father's sister"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) and the pl. of this is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~aAtN","text_ar":"عَمَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bona Eam~iY","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَ عَمِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA Abn Eam~i","text_ar":"يا ابن عَمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA Abn Eam~a","text_ar":"يا ابن عَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA Abn Eami","text_ar":"يا ابن عَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, [but in one copy of the S I find the first three and not the last,]) the last without teshdeed, (L,) dial. vars. [all meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O son of my paternal uncle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, L:) and Abu-n-Nejm uses the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bonapa","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~aA","text_ar":"عَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O daughter of my paternal uncle"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~aAho","text_ar":"عَمَّاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"of lamentation. (S.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA A@bonaA Eam~K","text_ar":"هُمَا ا@بْنَا عَمٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Each of them two is a son of a paternal uncle of the other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, IB, Msb, K;) because each of them says to the other,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA","text_ar":"يَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bona Eam~iY","text_ar":"ا@بْنَ عَمِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IB;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonaA xaAlapK","text_ar":"ا@بْنَا خَالَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, IB, Msb, K;) because each of them says to the other,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bona jaAlatiY","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَ جَالَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IB:) but one may not say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA A@bonaA Eam~apK","text_ar":"هُمَا ا@بْنَا عَمَّةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonaA xaAlK","text_ar":"ا@بْنَا خَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, IB, Msb, K;) because one of them says to the other,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bona","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAliY","text_ar":"خَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the latter says to the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bona","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~atiY","text_ar":"عَمَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IB.) And ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~N","text_ar":"عَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A paternal great uncle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: therefore] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA A@bonaA Eam~K","text_ar":"هُمَا ا@بْنَا عَمٍّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laH~FA","text_ar":"لَحًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are cousins on the father's side, closely related"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonaA xaAlapK","text_ar":"ا@بْنَا خَالَةٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laH~FA","text_ar":"لَحًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laH~FA","text_ar":"لَحًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonaA Eam~apK","text_ar":"ا@بْنَا عَمَّةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonaA xaAlK laH~FA","text_ar":"ا@بْنَا خَالٍ لَحًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A@bonu Eam~ihi ZahorFA","text_ar":"هُوَ ا@بْنُ عَمِّهِ ظَهْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is his cousin on the father's side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distantly related."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, in A and O and TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zhr","text_ar":"ظهر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~axolapa","text_ar":"النَّخْلَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akorimuwA Eam~atakumu","text_ar":"اَكْرِمُوا عَمَّتَكُمُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Honour ye your paternal aunt the palm-tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e. [do ye so] because it was created of the redundant portion of the earth, or clay, of Adam. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~N","text_ar":"عَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall palm-trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of full tallness and abundance and density;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eum~N","text_ar":"عُمٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K, TA:) [or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxolu Eam~N","text_ar":"نَخْلُ عَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eum~N","text_ar":"عُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is perhaps meant in the K: for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eum~N","text_ar":"عُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet applied to palm-trees, (S, K, TA,) and is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiymapN","text_ar":"عَمِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiymN","text_ar":"عَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"All"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbs such as are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$ob","text_ar":"عُشْب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Th, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K","Msb","Sb","CK","L","IB"]},{"entry_id":"n30455","headword_ar":"عُمٌّ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~N","text_ar":"عَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumumN","text_ar":"عُمُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30619","headword_ar":"عَمٍ","root":"EmY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiYN","text_ar":"عَمِىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEomaY","text_ar":"اَعْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}